JMPD officers received a tip-off about the alleged corrupt examiner at the Xavier testing station and arrested him on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG – A licensing examiner will appear in a Johannesburg court on Wednesday after allegedly accepting a R5,000 bribe to pass a learner driver without doing the test. Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) officers received a tip-off about the corrupt examiner at the Xavier testing station and arrested him on Tuesday. JMPD's Wayne Minnaar says: “The examiner, who’s in his 40s, is likely to appear in court today on charges of bribery and corruption.”